<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 12:45:20 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>美国人如何看待特朗普处理贸易和关税的方式</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/01/how-americans-view-trumps-handling-of-trade-and-tariffs/</link><description>近十分之六的美国成年人不相信特朗普能够就贸易政策做出正确的决定。自 2025 年以来，美国与中国、加拿大和墨西哥之间的贸易观点发生了变化。</description><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 01:12:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/04/01/how-americans-view-trumps-handling-of-trade-and-tariffs/</guid></item><item><title>美国式的出生公民权在世界各地并不常见</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/us-style-birthright-citizenship-is-uncommon-around-the-world/</link><description>世界上还有 32 个国家/地区的出生权利公民身份法律与美国基本相似。另外 50 个左右的国家/地区的出生权利公民身份的变化更为有限。</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 01:22:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/us-style-birthright-citizenship-is-uncommon-around-the-world/</guid></item><item><title>2023 年美国约 9% 的新生儿是未经授权或临时合法移民母亲出生的</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/about-9-of-us-births-in-2023-were-to-unauthorized-or-temporary-legal-immigrant-mothers/</link><description>一般来说，非法移民的出生趋势随着非法移民人口的增长和减少而变化。</description><pubDate>Wed, 01 Apr 2026 01:07:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/31/about-9-of-us-births-in-2023-were-to-unauthorized-or-temporary-legal-immigrant-mothers/</guid></item><item><title>许多拉丁美洲人——尤其是新教徒——看到宗教在国家领导、身份和法律中的作用</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/26/many-latin-americans-especially-protestants-see-a-role-for-religion-in-national-leadership-identity-and-laws/</link><description>巴西、哥伦比亚和秘鲁的大多数人希望领导人能够维护自己的宗教信仰。新教徒在公共生活中特别支持基督教。</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 01:14:23 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/26/many-latin-americans-especially-protestants-see-a-role-for-religion-in-national-leadership-identity-and-laws/</guid></item><item><title>全美宗教电台</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/data-labs/2026/03/26/religious-radio-across-america/</link><description>几乎所有美国成年人都居住在宗教广播电台的覆盖范围内，最常见的是基督教广播电台。电台往往主要播放音乐或主要播放谈话。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 12:46:58 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/data-labs/2026/03/26/religious-radio-across-america/</guid></item><item><title>荷兰将同性婚姻合法化 25 年后，全球同性婚姻的重要事实</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/25/key-facts-about-same-sex-marriage-around-the-world-25-years-after-the-netherlands-legalized-it/</link><description>在首次全国承认同性婚姻二十五年后，现在已有近 40 个地方允许同性婚姻。但它们的流行程度各不相同，公众的态度也各不相同。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 01:15:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/25/key-facts-about-same-sex-marriage-around-the-world-25-years-after-the-netherlands-legalized-it/</guid></item><item><title>美国人普遍反对美国对伊朗采取军事行动</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/03/25/americans-broadly-disapprove-of-u-s-military-action-in-iran/</link><description>大多数美国人表示，打击伊朗是错误的决定，并且不赞成特朗普处理冲突的方式，党派分歧严重。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 01:00:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/03/25/americans-broadly-disapprove-of-u-s-military-action-in-iran/</guid></item><item><title>250 岁的美国：过去 50 年国家发生了怎样的变化</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2026/03/25/the-united-states-at-250-how-the-country-has-changed-in-the-past-50-years/</link><description>在美国 250 岁生日之际，根据 50 年来的人口普查数据，探索自 1976 年以来人口统计、工作、家庭和经济发生了怎样的变化。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 00:45:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2026/03/25/the-united-states-at-250-how-the-country-has-changed-in-the-past-50-years/</guid></item><item><title>美国人在建国 250 周年之前如何看待种族多样性</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/25/how-americans-value-racial-diversity-ahead-of-the-countrys-250th-anniversary/</link><description>75% 的美国成年人认为多样性对国家来说是一件好事，但民主党和共和党在多样性如何影响国家文化方面存在巨大分歧。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Mar 2026 00:30:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/25/how-americans-value-racial-diversity-ahead-of-the-countrys-250th-anniversary/</guid></item><item><title>美国人首先从哪里获取突发新闻信息？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/24/where-do-americans-turn-first-for-information-about-breaking-news/</link><description>当突发新闻事件发生时，36% 的美国成年人表示，他们通常会首先向自己喜欢的新闻机构寻求更多信息。</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 01:09:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/24/where-do-americans-turn-first-for-information-about-breaking-news/</guid></item></channel></rss>